'''''Twelve Tribes''''' is an album by the American musician [[Richard Souther]], released in 1990 on the Narada Equinox label. 

==Reception==
In a contemporaneous review, Jim Aikin described the album as "terrific".  He also noted that "Souther's compositional touch is unfaltering", giving specific praise to the "Compañero" track.<ref>Aikin, Jim, "In Review" ''Keyboard'' Volume 17, Number 7 (Issue #181) May 1991, page 17 </ref>

Linda Kohanov's review at AllMusic noted a "marked evolution in style" from previous albums, and commented that "Souther's creative use of ethnic rhythms and instruments adds a new level of sophistication to his accessibility".<ref name="Allmusic">Kohanov, L [http://www.allmusic.com/album/twelve-tribes-mw0000309459 AllMusic review]</ref>

